reviews.review_text: I m just a simple American white guy and this is authentic Chinese food I ordered the peppered steak with rice because I like simple Chinese food lol and they have everything on their menu. Things that I ve never heard of or even thought of but that s another story but I can tell you this I love spicy food, and this food is fantastic, I will absolutely come here and probably order the same dish cause I m too afraid to venture out to something else but it is got so much flavor and the quality is unbelievable. I m gonna bring my church group here. I ll try to add a photo but I already started eating , but it is fantastic

Great food,    Lobster butter and cream, crispy chicken on top of sticky rice, fried rice, you name it and Haiyi did it to perfection. I attended a 100 day celebration      here and the food was on point. My family loved it and were coming back for sure!

Reasonable place to get takeout dimsum. Parking is a bit difficult but there are fewer people going to eat now so its not as bad. If your going to eat in , the restaurant appears less dense than before and relatively more spaced. Pan fried daikon was good.

Fantastic food here, decent prices and nice staff. The old standards are great at this place. My personal favorite are the bbq pork buns as they remind me of the ones from Tim Ho Wan in hk. Dont want to give this place 5 stars (selfishly) as I dont want more  people coming here.
Good food and service. Reasonable price. Easy parking. Parking: easy

Delicious <3 Taro dishes were very yummy~! Tea was also good, and free if you eat before 11:30am on weekday. You can also get a baby dog for only 2$ if you spend a certain amount. Very worth it, very cute.

Great Chinese authentic restaurant. Fantastic service. Friendly staff. We had the crabs, eggplant with scallops and tofu, their specialty steam oysters, and house special soy sauce chicken. I know my Chinese cuisine and have very high standard.  This restaurant for sure has everything from food to service.  The atmosphere is very family and large crowd oriented.
Good quality of food and friendly staffs. I love the crispy tofu there. Price is good. If people like canton style seafood is a perfect place.
Delicious authentic Chinese Cuisine. Both quality of the food and service are good. Reasonable price. Highly recommend this restaurant.
Good dim sum and fair price. My top pick for dim sum in Vancouver.

Have been dining here with friends and family since it became Haiyi. Excellent service, the staff are always nice and friendly and goes above and beyond. Food is very good and pricing is reasonable. They are serving up a new salad made with ice crystal plant and chinese pears, so refreshing and delicious a must try. They only carry small quantities and cannot be had anywhere else.
Good dim sum
Pretty good food with reasonable price.

Awesome place to have lunch and dim sum. Very authentic. Great service. Definitely a delicacy. Most recommended dish is the shrimp scallop dim sum. My personal favorite. They offer local Guangzhou beer if you fancy that with dim sum. I prefer the regular Jasmine tea or puer is good too. They have a selection of 6 teas to choose from. All you have to do is ask.

I really like this place for dim sum. I havent gone for dinner yet but I do plan to soon. They have a pretty good selection of food and the quality is amazing. One of the few chinese restaurants that take my allergies to green onions seriously. That makes me super happy. My parents love this place too. The servers are very friendly and I find them more polite than most places!

There are many Chinese seafood restaurants - however, its great to find one which really has distinctive flavour in the dishes served. Whether it is a rice dish or a noodle dish, the feature topping them is truly a savour of fine cooking. I shall return - with friends.

Good attentive service.  It gets fairly busy here during lunch and dinner hours so be prepared for a little wait.  They serve traditional Chinese banquet style dishes and offer fresh seafood.   Definitely one of the decent places to go in this area of town.

The food here is some of the best in Vancouver with fresh, tasty dim sum and wonderful Chinese dishes. We have had both small and large parties here and the service has always been great. I would say that Haiyi is without doubt my favorite dim sum restaurant in Vancouver. It might even be better than Hong Kong! Give yourself a treat and try it out. There is also free parking in the front if its not too busy. Its obviously a very sincere place.
Great tasting dim sum. I go to this restaurant all the time. They also dont charge for tea and give a 20% discount off your bill, from Mon-Fri from 9:30am -11:30am.
I come here for dim sum.  Rumor has it is the chef is from another well loved Chinese restaurant.  A good variety, and nice portions.   Make sure you ask for their homemade XO sauce.
Dim sum is good.  Durian mochi is superb and they were the best I have ever had.  They make it fresh right after you ordered!
We were there recently for dinner and a while back for dim sum.  Both times food were great also great service.  Definitely recommend!
Helpful and attentive service! Was very satisfied with our dim sum lunch. Would definitely recommend.
Very efficient and nice servers. In addition to the delicious foods. The must try item I would recommend the black sesame seed pudding.
Chef came from Marine and Fraser. Best BEST BEST golden fried tofu. Feels comoletely satisfied. Done. Just bring me some rice.
Great food!  They have some innovative dishes imo. A little tight on space though. Will go again.
Only had take out. Their dimsum is nice and the best dish i have tried is the soy sauce chicken. Gorgeous.
Cantonese restaurant with very good Dim sum. Other Cantonese dishes are also done well. Mandarin/Sichuan style are cooked from a Cantonese perspective.
Haiyi is a great place for Cantonese-style Chinese food. Food is pretty good. Very authentic food, feels like a restaurant in Hong Kong.
Good, reasonably priced early morning dim sum.
Really tasty crab special with vermicelli at a competitive price. Friendly staff members as well.
Parking in front of restaurant and on street. Reasonable priced menu.
Reasonable price, big portions and delicious still in busiest time
very good food
The food is consistently very good. It is our regular go to restaurant.
Excellent quality and very good price.  Place is busy and not too crowded.

Good dim sum. Parking available. Reasonable prices.
Gets busy at night on weekends. Good food thats not too oily.
Great resteraunt. Highly recommended for Hong Kong style food.
Tasty stuff. I didnt pay for the meal and have no idea what it cost.
Good restaurant, I have been there several times.
Food is good and service is good.  Thanks Carol s recommendations

Lots of choice on menu and reasonable price

I love their dumplings, a lot of Chinese people visit here. It s reasonable price. Good Chinese restaurants on Main Street. Recommend! I recommend to book before coming as well.

Not bad! The price is fair! The food has improved! It s even better! The service is very good
Great taste   Shiqi pigeon

Go to Haiyi Seafood Restaurant on the first day of the second day of the new year and order a roast chicken in the left pot. The skin is crispy and the meat slides down. The glutinous rice is fried until it is crispy!!! Ordered crispy chicken with sticky rice that s super tasty! Will go again for sure!
The restaurant has a comfortable environment, attentive service, diverse dishes, and delicious taste. It is a good place for drinking tea and eating.
The store is not big but the food is delicious I passed by by chance and came in to try something new. My family was very satisfied with it. Add to pocket list
After eating three times, the quality and quantity are guaranteed, very good!
